The true depth of a story is almost always hidden within the details. Such is the inspiration behind our newest StockX video series, taking a closer look at the aspects that elevate a sneaker from just a piece of footwear to cultural artifact. And the truth is that there might not be a better first pair to kick this off than the colette Air Jordan 1.

A shoe that was born out of a special, private collaboration between Jordan Brand and colette, this shoe actually never released and was a gift from Jordan to colette as a Friends & Family exclusive, paying tribute to their 20 years of business.

Enjoy taking a closer look at these legendary shoes, and if you want to own a pair, make sure to donate to @Oceana on @StockX via the link in our bio before Friday, December 20, 2019. #coletteforever

Trading for over $400, the 2019-20 Panini Prizm Basketball Hobby Box is perfect for any collector. This week we're giving you the chance to win your very own! Head over to @StockXTradingCards to follow, like their post, and tag 3 friends to enter the giveaway. Link in bio for official rules.

Originally created for employees of the Paris store, the colette Air Jordan 1 is one of the rarest colorways ever produced and is coveted around the world. Now, we’re giving you the chance to get one of the last 30 pairs in existence and to help preserve and restore the world's oceans for only $20.

All you have to do is make a $20 donation between now and 11:59PM EST on Friday, December 20, 2019 to be entered for your chance to own a pair. All net proceeds benefit @Oceana, an organization committed to ocean conservation. Hit the link in our bio to learn more. #coletteforever (Available to legal residents of the US, UK, Germany, and France who are 18 years of age or older. Rules at link in bio.)
